# quick-smoke-entrypoint design

## Accepted behavior

The desired behavior is the current summary-and-links flow:

1. check the canonical manual-smoke docs referenced by `MANUAL_SMOKE_DOC_PATHS`
2. if any doc is missing, write an explicit error and stop
3. otherwise run the bounded docs contract test
4. print the short smoke summary plus canonical doc links

## Implementation notes

- keep the entrypoint in `scripts/smoke.mjs`
- keep the docs contract in `tests/contracts/manual-smoke-harness-docs.test.ts`
- use lightweight dependency injection in `runSmokePreflight()` only as needed to verify the missing-doc runtime path without changing CLI scope
